nd Lange have also examined and extensively integrated the written records to amplify and cross-check their findings. Based on the methodologies of archaeology, history, and ethnography, Plantation Slavery in Barbados explores new ways to reconstruct the culture of a social group that left few historical records. As a description of the organization and development of the plantation system in Barbados, it is a model work in the burgeoning fields of slavery studies, historical anthropology, and Caribbean history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAntiquities. 0aGeschichte Nordamerikas. 0aOpgravingen. 0aPlantages. 0aPlantation life. 0aSlavernij. 0aSlavery. 4aBarbados -- Antiquities. 4aHISTORY / Latin America / General. 4aPlantation life -- Barbados -- History. 4aSlavery -- Barbados -- History. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aLange, Frederick W., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRiordan, Robert V.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: World History eBook Packagez9783110353563oZDB-23-HWH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067433235540uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067433236240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674332362423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674332362.jpg  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-HCO  aZDB-23-HWH